column1: we had a HUGE number of carp that died off this spring. There were ~ 30-40 eagles spotted around the lake but they got sick of eating fish so 8 people who live on this lake collected ~ 1000 rotting carp and fertilized a local farmers field.  A lot of fish remained in the lake despite our efforts.

column2: calm and sunny water lever down quite a bit from last month.
water level stays down despite adequate rainfall.  The dam downstream must be wide open draining out this lake!!
sunny.  Lake water level continues to be quite low.

column1: There was a lot of "new" plant growth seen this year in areas that I have never seen vegetation before.  Possibly because of the lack of carp
